==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[voluptuosus]], ''delightful'', from [[volup]], ''with pleasure''.
ú===Adjective===
'''voluptuous'''

#suggestive of full, generous, pleasurable vision or sensation

#(female) possessing a curvaceous figure: ample breasts, small waist, curvy hips, shapely legs and a round backside

